The paper focuses on designing an interaction scenario with a robotic tutor for an inquiry-based learning task, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of a robotic tutor also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The study also involves the use of a robot (cs.RO) and explores the effectiveness of different strategies for tutoring, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) as it relates to the security of the learning process.
